toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> New =
York Times reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Late Thursday, he fired Twitter=E2=80=99s chie=
f executive, chief financial officer and other executives. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Musk also appears unlikely to pay the gold=
en parachutes that the fired top executives of Twitter were set to receive.=
 Under the merger agreement, those executives =E2=80=94 including Parag Agr=
awal, the chief executive =E2=80=94 had been set to receive compensation of=
 $20 million to $60 million if they were fired. But Mr. Musk terminated the=
 executives =E2=80=9Cfor cause,=E2=80=9D meaning he did it because he alleg=
ed he had justification, which may void that agreement, two people with kno=
wledge of the matter said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those executives, who also include the former =
chief financial officer Ned Segal, the former general counsel Sean Edgett, =
and the former top policy and legal executive Vijaya Gadde, are deliberatin=
g their next steps, one person said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/29546575.290502/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvZTg=
wYjAyMTMtZDlkNC00MjdkLTk0ZDUtNGQ5YWVkZjE3YmM4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa49b=
