<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Some more Oh Elon</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He=E2=80=99s got a tight schedule for <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29546575.290502/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMjkvbXVzay1wcmVwYXJl=
cy1mb3Itam9iLWN1dHMtYXQtdHdpdHRlcj9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDMxMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1=
fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjEwMzEmdXRtX2=
NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB80d3e076" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  firi=
ng everybody else</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk has begun laying the groundwork for =
a round of layoffs at Twitter Inc. days after taking ownership of the socia=
l media platform.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The billionaire entrepreneur, who completed hi=
s $44 billion acquisition Thursday, has asked managers to draw up lists of =
team members who could be let go, according to a person with knowledge of t=
he matter. The person asked not to be identified discussing private convers=
ations.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29546575.290502/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8xMC8yOS90=
ZWNobm9sb2d5L3R3aXR0ZXItbGF5b2Zmcy1tdXNrLWpvYnMuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cC48977cd0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">And</a>:=C2=A0</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The layoffs at Twitter would take =
place before a Nov. 1 date when employees were scheduled to receive stock g=
rants as part of their compensation. Such grants typically represent a sign=
ificant portion of employees=E2=80=99 pay. By laying off workers before tha=
t date, Mr. Musk may avoid paying the grants, though he is supposed to pay =
the employees cash in place of their stock under the terms of the merger ag=
reement.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Charming. What a strange deal. Ordinarily when=
 a public company gets acquired, one of two things happens:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It is a strategic deal, the buyer is =
also a company in a similar line of business, and there are months of integ=
ration planning before the deal closes. The managers of the buyer=E2=80=99s=
 ad-sales and data-security and whatever departments meet with the target=
=E2=80=99s ad-sales and data-security and whatever departments, and figure =
out what they=E2=80=99re doing, and get some sense of who they will keep an=
d who will be redundant. The buyer=E2=80=99s CEO has people she trusts to m=
ake these sorts of employment and business decisions, and they get to make =
those decisions about the target.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footn=
ote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !i=
mportant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;"=
>
<span>[4]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It is a private-equity-type deal,=
 the buyer is a financial buyer, and generally the buyer=E2=80=99s executiv=
es show up on the first day after the merger closes and say =E2=80=9Cwe thi=
nk you=E2=80=99re doing a great job and we have no immediate plans to chang=
e anything, we just want you to do it even=C2=A0better.=E2=80=9D And then t=
hey spend a few months getting the lay of the land and getting to know whic=
h managers to trust, and=C2=A0<em>then=C2=A0</em>they start laying people o=
ff.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tr=
ansparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here, the buyer is a guy. It=E2=80=99s Elon Mu=
sk. It is not another social media company, there are no real overlaps, he =
has no social media lieutenants who can decide whom to lay off. But he is n=
ot a hands-off financial buyer either: He has strong views about product an=
d wants to make huge changes all at once. And he did basically no integrati=
on planning, because until a few weeks ago he was still trying to avoid clo=
sing the deal. But now he=E2=80=99s going to get rid of thousands of employ=
ees in a couple of days? How?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One possible answer is that he is going to mee=
t individually with each of Twitter=E2=80=99s 7,500 employees, interview th=
em, review their work, and decide personally whether they can keep their jo=
bs. This would be utterly insane, for a man who runs multiple companies and=
 surely has better things to do, but =E2=80=9Cthis would be utterly insane=
=E2=80=9D is never a good reason to doubt anything about this deal, and <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29546575.290502/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cucGxhdGZvcm1lci5uZXdzL3AvZWxvbi10YWtlcy1vdmVyLXR3aXR0ZXI/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cBdc89b59b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> here is Casey Newton</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Engineers were told to prepare for =E2=80=9Cco=
de pairing=E2=80=9D with Musk, in which they would sit with him and review =
code together.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just after noon [Friday], an executive assista=
nt asked engineers to begin preparing code to show to Musk.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CPlease print out 50 pages of code you=
=E2=80=99ve done in the last 30 days (if you haven=E2=80=99t submitted code=
 in the past 30 days, then you can go back up to 60 days),=E2=80=9D the ass=
istant wrote in a Slack message obtained by Platformer. =E2=80=9CPlease be =
ready to show on your computer as well.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CRecency of code is important but also=
 use a code that shows complexity of our code,=E2=80=9D she added.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By mid-afternoon, printouts were seen everywhe=
re at Twitter headquarters, I=E2=80=99m told.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In mid-afternoon, the instruction changed agai=
n. A notice went out to employees ordering them to cease printing out their=
 code, for reasons that were not immediately clear.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CUPDATE: Stop printing,=E2=80=9D read =
another bolded notice obtained by Platformer. =E2=80=9CPlease be ready to s=
how your recent code (within last 30-60 preferably) on your computer. If yo=
u have already printed, please shred in the bins on SF-Tenth. Thank you!=E2=
=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So far I=E2=80=99ve been unable to speak with =
anyone who actually underwent one of these pop quizzes with Musk; one sourc=
e said the meetings keep getting delayed.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Right, I mean, is Musk actually going to meet =
with every engineer at Twitter and fire the ones whose=C2=A0code printouts =
he finds insufficiently elegant? No, come on, of course not. Is he going to=
 pretend he=E2=80=99ll do that, for reasons of his own? Sure, whatever.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other possibility is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0well, =
Musk=C2=A0<em>does=C2=A0</em>run a big public company that employs engineer=
s; maybe <em>they=C2=A0</em>can do the Twitter integration planning and dec=
ide whose code is sufficiently elegant. That big public company is Tesla In=
c., which makes cars, and which has other public shareholders, and whose en=
gineers seem to work pretty hard on the cars. But can they take some time a=
way from the cars to help their boss with his personal hobby? Bloomberg=E2=
=80=99s Kurt Wagner and Edward Ludlow <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
